There are 3 layers in the structure on the right, while the structure on the left has 2.  Blocks are arranged in various configurations: some are placed next to others, while others are placed on top of each other.  The spatial relationships are crucial for determining the order of assembly.  The orientations of the blocks (e.g., horizontal, vertical, angled) are clearly visible.
